    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Martial Arts Handbook pg. 30</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 200 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 8 lbs</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d10 (small), 2d6 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> S; <strong>Special</strong> Disarm, trip, see text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Blades, Heavy</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>Patterned after the fiery blades masterfully wielded by Sarenite angels, the split-blade sword is both a holy symbol and a difficult-yet-effective weapon. A split-blade sword resembles a large scimitar whose blade splits into two about two-thirds of the way toward the tip. If your Dexterity score is less than 15, you take a -2 penalty on attacks rolls with a split-blade sword, as you're unable to maneuver its unusual blade.</p>",
